The difference between JPA and Hibernate
=The main difference between JPA and Hibernate is the fact that JPA is a specification.
 =It is a set of rules and guidelines to set interfaces for implementing object-relational mapping, .
 =Dynamic and named queries can be included in JPA.
==========================================================
 Hibernate is Red Hatâ€™s implementation of the JPA spec.
 It helps in mapping Java data types to SQL data types.
  Hibernate is an ORM framework that sits between the application and the database



